          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1715605152534-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1715605152534-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated</strong> <strong>chicken</strong> and cook for 9 min on each side pressing down firmly with a spatula until the outside is golden and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your<strong> Cajun-style free range chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1715605156166-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1715605156166-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1715605156166-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1715605156166-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1715605156166-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>cider vinegar </strong>and<strong> </strong>a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> in a bowl with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, <strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Add your <strong>shredded red cabbage</strong>, <strong>grated carrot</strong> and <strong>half</strong> the <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>spring onion</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to the bowl and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>red cabbage slaw</strong></p><p>Combine your <strong>mayo</strong> and <strong>red</strong> <strong>chilli relish </strong>in a bowl – this is your <strong>chilli mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1715605160630-x200.jpg",
